<body>
<p>ISP software:
<ul>
<li><a href="https://github.com/rfc1036/rpsltool">rpsltool</a> is a BGP 
filters generator
based on <a href="http://www.template-toolkit.org/">Template::Toolkit</a>.
<li><a href="cisco-tools-0.3.tgz">cisco-tools</a>: arpwatcher, checkdualif,
cisco-cmd, dumppeers, routesdiff, update-list, drop. 
A collection of random programs which may or may not be useful to people 
managing Cisco routers.
</ul>

<p>Usenet-related software:
<ul>
<li><a href="autoresponder.tgz">autoresponder.tgz</a> is a new autoresponder
for test groups, with replies rate limiting.
<li><a href="robomod.tgz">moderatore</a> is a very old snapshot of my perl
robomoderator based on News::Gateway.
<li><a href="cmsg-tools.tgz">cmsg-tools</a> is a collection of scripts
I use to generate control messages for the it.* and linux.* hierarchies.
<li><a href="News-ICC-0.2.tar.gz">News::ICC</a> is a perl implementation
of the inndcom.c library (the same used by ctlinnd).
<li><a href="News-Nocem-0.1.tgz">News::Nocem</a> is a perl module useful
for generating nocem notices.
<li><a href="newsdist.pl.gz">NewsDist</a> shows how your feeds are connected
(buggy).
<li><a href="inndelay.pl.gz">inndelay.pl</a> displays a graph of articles
propagation time (original version by Fabien Tassin).
<li><a href="gpgverify.gz">gpgverify</a> is like pgpverify but uses GnuPG
(not much useful now that pgpverify uses GnuPG too).
<li><a href="inews.c.gz">inews.c</a> is a light and simple inews
implementation.
</ul>

<p>Jabber-related software:
<ul>
<li><a href="headlines4.pl.gz">headlines4.pl</a> is a jabber component
which distributes RSS headlines.
<li><a href="presence-0.8.tgz">presence</a> provides web presence icons.
</ul>

<p><a href="../irssi/">Some irssi scripts I wrote or modified.</a>

<p>Other software:
<ul>
<li><a href="https://github.com/rfc1036/whois">whois</a>
(<a href="http://ftp.debian.org/debian/pool/main/w/whois/">releases</a>)
is an improved whois client.
It is part of Debian, Fedora, SuSE, PLD and other Linux distributions.
<li><a href="https://github.com/rfc1036/zebra-dump-parser">zebra-dump-parser</a> is a parser for
the binary packet dump format of zebra and MRT. It can be used to parse
BGP dumps from <a href="http://data.ris.ripe.net/">RIPE RIS</a> or
<a href="http://www.routeviews.org/">routeviews</a>.
<li><a href="switchsh.c.gz">switchsh</a> is a tiny program which can be
used to temporarily change /bin/sh only for its child processes.
It shows how to use bind mounts, CLONE_NEWNS and the clone(2) and
unshare(2) Linux system calls.
<li><a href="multicast-tools.tgz">multicast-tools</a> is a collection of
simple programs which can be used to test multicast connectivity.
<li><a href="bindgraph-0.2.tgz">bindgraph</a> is a tool that makes
pretty graphs about queries sent to your BIND name server.
(<a href="bindgraph-0.1.tgz">bindgraph 0.1</a> supports BIND &lt; 9.3.)
<li><a href="setlimits.c.gz">setlimits.c</a> is a trivial helper program
which raises some system limits and then drops privileges before spawning
another program. It's used on servers of the freenode IRC network.
<li><a href="spam-stats.pl.gz">spam-stats.pl</a> is a postfix log analyzer.
<li><a href="../6to4">6to4</a> is a simple script to enable instant IPv6
connectivity on Linux.
<li>I refactored the old lbnamed perl load balancing name server in
what later became
<a href="http://www.stanford.edu/~riepel/lbnamed/Stanford-DNSserver/">Stanford::DNSserver</a>.
</ul>

<p>Hacks of dubious utility:
<ul><a href="trenitalia2csv.gz">trenitalia2csv</a>: converte in CSV l'elenco
dei biglietti ferroviari acquistati con Cartaviaggio.
</ul>

<p>Useless and/or obsolete software:
<ul>
<li><a href="vacation_3.3.0.tar.gz">vacation</a> is an improved vacation
program.
<li><a href="tinyrmail.c.gz">tinyrmail.c</a> is a small rmail implementation
intended for use with postfix or other domainized MTAs. It does add a
Received header to help identification of the remote UUCP system.
<li><a href="ssd.tgz">start-stop-daemon</a> with capabilities support.
<li><a href="mdmda-991121.tgz">MdMDA</a> is a minimalist mail delivery
agent for big sites. It supports virtual users, maildirs, quotas and
hashed spool directories. Think of it as a programming exercise.
<li><a href="formail.diff.gz">formail.diff</a> is a small patch to
formmail.pl which you can use to create a spam honeypot.
<li><a href="readdir-wrapper.tgz">readdir-wrapper.tgz</a> is a library
which can be used to make long find(1) runs less heavy on busy systems.
<li><a href="lockvt.c.gz">lockvt.c</a> is a console locker for Linux systems.
</ul>

</body>
